ted by coriolis effects. It takes considerable force to retract that weight while spinning. In fact it takes the exact amount of force to retract it as is created on the other side with the increased force from the lenthened stroke. Opposite and equal reaction, interestingly enough, the way he tested the device would create all kinds of complex reactions to the ground, but would still probably thrust right along as the video shows. It would never work in a weightless environment. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=drcarstairs>DrCarstairs</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Utterly Mad Scientist</span><br>  Posts: 225<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(6/25/03 1:31 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=338.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/rant/AVitW/images/bioh.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  ASPS and AGSPRI</span><hr size=1> Well, I don’t speak Italian so I cannot delve into the ASPS site (I can use translators, but frankly I am not that impressed with it). A page on the purported reactionless thruster is in English, and though I cannot comment of technical details (as none are provided) I can point out a few “Red Flag” words that indicate the possibility of deception:<br>
“system closed in a box” – you cannot see what we have made. <br>
“specific impulse is very high” – its super keen powerful, but…<br>
“low and very long thrust” – it cannot move on earth, so you have to take our word for it.<br>
“no propellant consumption” – Its MAGIC!<br>
“Very low system mass and overall dimensions” – no need for large, heavy parts because…<br>
“Absence of moving parts” – its an empty box.<br>
<br>
As for the video from AGSPRI, it is crappy quality and shows what appears to be this saucer (ever notice how many of these reactionless schemes use saucers?) knocking itself across the floor. Yale is dead on about their technobabble, it gave me a headache just scanning the page the video is on – these guys should write Star Trek episodes. Basically its crap.<br>
